//             Experiment No.4: Embedding Audio and Video in a Web Page

a. Embed audio files in a web page using the <audio> element with multiple source formats. 
b. Embed video files in a web page using the <video> element with controls and multiple source formats. 
c. Understand the use of attributes like controls, autoplay, loop, and muted for audio and video playback.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Audio and Video</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#fff0ff">
    <h2>Audio Example</h2>
    <audio controls>
        <source src="awaz.mp3" type="audio/mp3">
        Your browser does not support audio elements
    </audio>

    <hr>

    <h2>Video Example 1</h2>
    <video width="320" height="240" controls>
        <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        Your browser does not support video elements
    </video>

    <h2>Video Example 2</h2>
    <video width="640" height="360" controls autoplay muted loop>
        <source src="itachi.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        Your browser does not support video elements
    </video>
</body>
</html>
